author: Corinne Abrams
title: In Pictures: India’s Republic Day Parades
text:
0 COMMENTS 
India celebrated its 68th Republic Day on Thursday, with Prime Minister Narendra Modi hosting Sheikh Mohamed bin Zayed Al Nahyan, Crown Prince of Abu Dhabi, for events in New Delhi.
The crown prince was treated to a showcase of India’s military might during a parade along Raj Path, the city’s ceremonial boulevard, while other celebrations took place across the country.
Here are some highlights:
ENLARGE A contingent of the elite National Security Guard marched during the 68th Republic Day Parade in New Delhi, India, Jan. 26, 2017. Photo: Partha Sarkar/Zuma Press 
ENLARGE School children during Republic Day celebrations in Ajmer, Rajasthan, Jan. 26, 2017. Photo: Zuma Press 
ENLARGE Indian Air Force fighter jets flew past over during the 68th Republic Day Parade in New Delhi, India, Jan. 26, 2017. Photo: Partha Sarkar/Xinhua/Zuma Press 
ENLARGE The 68th Republic Day Parade in New Delhi, India, Jan. 26, 2017. 
ENLARGE Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi waved to spectators after the Republic Day Parade at Rajpath in New Delhi, Jan. 26, 2017. Photo: Prakash Singh/Agence France-Presse/Getty Images 
ENLARGE Indian schoolchildren performed during a cultural event held to celebrate Republic Day in Bangalore, India, Jan. 26, 2017. Photo: Jagadeesh Nv/European Pressphoto Agency 
ENLARGE A United Arab Emirates military contingent marched during the parade in New Delhi, India, Jan. 26, 2017. Photo: European Pressphoto Agency 
ENLARGE Policemen performed traditional Indian gymnastics during a Republic Day parade in Allahabad, India, Jan. 26, 2017. Photo: Jitendra Prakash/Reuters
